WHO   — NOUTHESIA — a UD0 universe — the admonition
WHAT  — NOUTHESIA — the warnings: 1984's boot, Brave New World's pleasure, Fahrenheit 451's distraction, and Animal Farm's betrayed revolution, read on the axis of how freedom dies.
WHERE — the Greek νουθεσία, ‘a warning meant to teach’ — literally to put a thing in someone's mind so they correct course  Framework inputs: Orwell's 1984 & Animal Farm; Huxley's Brave New World; Bradbury's Fahrenheit 451; Neil Postman's Huxley-vs-Orwell thesis  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)
WHY   — Because the dystopia is the purest form of nouthesia — a vivid, terrible example offered so we will choose differently while we still can.
HOW   — A universe that gathers the great dystopias as admonitions: books written not to predict but to warn — ‘learn this lesson before you live it.’

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  νουθεσία — these books are not predictions but admonitions: learn the lesson, the authors beg, before you have to live it.

